<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF108-425-420  </DOCNO><DOCID>08 425 420.andM;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Newsbytes  May 1 1990* Full Text COPYRIGHT Newsbytes Inc. 1990.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Microsoft offers unique corporate support plan.andO;</TITLE><AUTHOR>McNamara, Sean.andM;</AUTHOR><DESCRIPT>Company:   Microsoft Corp. (services).andO;Ticker:    MSFT.andO;Topic:     Software PublishersMarketing StrategySupport ServicesDealers and AgentsCompaniesAustraliaCustomer RelationsVendor Relations.andM;</DESCRIPT><TEXT>MICROSOFT OFFERS UNIQUE CORPORATE SUPPORT PLAN SYDNEY, AUSTRALIA, 1990 APR 26(NB) -- Microsoft has announced a new support service through its CommuniqueClub.andP;  The support will be offered in two levels - corporate anddealer/developer.andM;The main feature of both levels is 25 hours of access time per year toMicrosoft OnLine, the personalised telephone support and electronicinformation retrieval and response system which is aimed at solving softwareproblems.andM;For AUS$19,500 a year, corporations also receive the personal support of asystems engineer whose job it is to understand the corporation's system andits needs, as well as present periodic talks on industry directions.andO;Corporations are also given a subscription to Micosoft's Systems Journal and10 free products annually for evaluation purposes.andP;  Companies are alsodesignated as beta test sites for future product offerings.andM;&quot;Microsoft Communique Access Support for Corporations offers a level ofsoftware and systems support unprecedented in Australia,&quot; said Daniel Petre,managing director of Microsoft Australia.andP;  &quot;Corporations often spend hundredsof thousands of dollars on hardware service and support but we are the firstsoftware company to offer this kind of support, and at a fraction of thecost.&quot;andM;Developers and dealers can subscribe at AUS$5,000 per year, and will receivethe OnLine access, as well as Microsoft's Systems Journal.andP;  &quot;There is awealth of knowledge accumulated from developers around the world available onthe database which will greatly assist local Australian developers in theirefforts.andP;  Dealers, too, stand to become better equipped to market Microsoft'sproduct range enhancing their knowledge through the Access Support program&quot;Petre said.andM;(Sean McNamara/19900427/Contact: Jennifer Zanich, phone in Australia+61-2-452 0100)</TEXT></DOC>